# shared-foundation — Overview

## Project identity
- **Type:** Kotlin Multiplatform **library** of **shared API contracts** consumed by **backend** and **client** (same serialized JSON shapes, path strings, and machine-readable error **code** strings).
- **Publishing:** Maven Central via `com.vanniktech.maven.publish`; version in root `build.gradle.kts`.
- **Coordinates:** group `io.github.mudrichenkoevgeny`; artifact ids follow `shared-foundation-*` (see `settings.gradle.kts` / published module paths).
- **Consumers:** not in this repo — [README.md](README.md): **[Backend Platform SDK](https://github.com/mudrichenkoevgeny/backend-platform-sdk)** (server), **[KMP Platform SDK](https://github.com/mudrichenkoevgeny/kmp-platform-sdk)** (client). This repo is the **lowest shared layer** of types both sides compile against.

## Tech stack
- **Kotlin** 2.x, **kotlinx.serialization** (`kotlinx-serialization-json`).
- **JSON defaults:** `FoundationJson` in `core/common` (`serialization/FoundationJson.kt`).
- **Targets:** per module `build.gradle.kts` (e.g. JVM, Android library, iOS, Wasm JS).
- **No UI layer** in this repository.

## Modules (`shared/foundation/`)

### `core/common`
- **Error wire shape:** `error/model/ApiErrorResponse` (`id`, `code`, `message`, `args` map); **not** a sealed exception hierarchy — `code` values align with `CommonErrorCodes` and feature-specific `*ErrorCodes` in other modules.
- **Error naming:** `error/naming/CommonErrorCodes`, `CommonErrorArgs` — string constants for JSON/logging parity.
- **Network:** `network/contract` (`CommonApiFields`, `CommonHttpHeaders`, `WebSocketContract`, …); `network/model/websocket` (`SocketFrame`, payloads such as `WebSocketInitializePayload`).
- **Domain:** e.g. `domain/model/UserClientType`.
- **Validation:** `validation/NetworkFieldAnnotations.kt` — JVM retention annotations for marking required/non-blank fields (interpretation lives in validators outside or alongside this lib).
- **Depends only on** kotlinx.serialization (see `build.gradle.kts`); **does not** depend on `feature/*`.

### `core/security`
- **Error naming:** `SecurityErrorCodes`, `SecurityErrorArgs`.
- **Password policy:** `passwordpolicy/` — `PasswordPolicy`, `PasswordPolicyValidator` (interface + `PasswordPolicyValidatorImpl`), `PasswordPolicyValidatorResult`, mappers, API responses.
- **Network:** security settings routes/requests/responses, `SecurityApiFields`, WebSocket event types for security.
- Gradle: **no** `api(project(":shared:foundation:core:common"))` today — self-contained module + serialization; `feature/user` pulls `core/common` separately.

### `core/settings`
- Global settings: routes, requests/responses, `GlobalSettingsApiFields`, settings WebSocket event types.

### `feature/user`
- **Error naming:** `UserErrorCodes`, `UserErrorArgs`.
- **Domain:** `domain/model` — roles, account status, auth providers, etc.
- **Network:** `network/route`, `request`, `response`, `contract` (paths, query params, user-specific API fields).
- **Depends on:** `api` `core/common`, `core/security`, `core/settings` (see `feature/user/build.gradle.kts`).

### `bom`
- Aligns versions of published `shared-foundation-*` artifacts for consumers.

## Boundaries
- **`core/common` must not** depend on `feature/*`.
- **`feature/*`** may aggregate multiple `core/*` modules; keep feature-only types out of `core/*` unless truly cross-cutting.
- **No** Ktor route implementations, HTTP client setup, or app entry points — only **types and constants** (and pure interfaces like `PasswordPolicyValidator` + default impl).
